    "These algorithms learn word embeddings by considering local context windows.",
    "GloVe utilizes both global and local context windows to generate word embeddings.",
    "This word embedding technique is trained on the nonzero elements of a word-word co-occurrence matrix (Pennington et al. 2014).",
    "Uto et al. (2020) employed GloVe to capture context information from essays, which was used in conjunction with handcrafted features for essay scoring.",
    "Cao et al. (2020) utilized 200-dimensional GloVe vectors to initialize the word embeddings in the HA-LSTM architecture for encoding essays."
